description:
The plugin-hook describe block in assets/opencode/plugins/test/context-usage.test.ts now has 6 tests that each repeat the same scaffolding:

  const mockFetch = vi.fn().mockImplementation(...)
  const hooks = await contextUsagePlugin(makeCtx(mockFetch) as any)
  const output = { system: ['existing header'] }
  await hooks['experimental.chat.system.transform']!(...)

The code reviewer flagged this in BOTH the Task 2 review (for the fetchLatestAssistantUsage describe block, 10 tests with similar boilerplate) and the Task 4 review. We deferred both times to stay within the bite-sized task boundaries.

Suggested refactor: extract a helper

  async function runHook(opts: {
    mockFetch?: typeof fetch
    model?: any
    sessionID?: string
    output?: { system: string[] }
  }): Promise<{ output: { system: string[] }, mockFetch: ReturnType<typeof vi.fn> }>

Then each test becomes:

  it('pushes a formatted usage line ...', async () => {
    const { output, mockFetch } = await runHook({
      mockFetch: vi.fn().mockImplementation(async () => new Response(...)),
    })
    expect(output.system[1]).toContain('187,234')
  })

Apply similar treatment to the helper-level describe block if it cleans up well.

Verify all 17 context-usage tests still pass and self-compact's 26 are untouched.

Low priority — purely a readability win, no behavior change. The current state ships fine; this is for the next time someone adds tests to this file.
